Enugu A Middle Aged man, Onyenwe Offor Ajah of Ameke Enu Oduma Aninri Local Government Area of Enugu State, has allegedly hacked his son, Kenneth Ajah, to death. DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered that the deceased was 38 years old as at the time of his death. According to sources in the community, trouble started at about 4.30pm on March 28, when the man had a disagreement with his son at Orie Oduma Market, Aninri LGA. The misunderstanding was said to have caused a fight between the aman and his son and in the process, the man picked up a sharp object and struck his son on the head. His son was said to have slumped on the ground and lost consciousness. The man escaped while his son was later confirmed dead. Ebere Amaraizu, the spokesman of Enugu State Police Command, confirmed the incident. Amaraizu, a Superintendent of Police, said the deceased’s body had been deposited at Awgu District General Hospital Mortuary while a manhunt for the fleeing suspect (his father) had been intensified. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.